{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reduce the electricity Green Levy for home Heat Pump owners to the same as gas ",
        "additional_details": "Plans to gradually equalise the green levies on gas and electricity have been shelved because of the energy crisis. Yet at the same time, Government seeks to encourage the uptake of heat pumps. Unfortunately, their running costs are a big disincentive for many and those costs are artificially increased by the x 10 difference between the \u2018green tax\u2019 treatment of gas and electricity even though electricity is greener.\r\n\r\nPlease stop penalising those who want to do the right thing by the planet!",
        "background": "Make heat pump ownership less expensive as a matter of urgency in order to encourage uptake and achieve zero-carbon earlier.\r\n\r\nThe electricity for them costs 4 times more than gas running an equivalent gas boiler. Heat pumps may be 3 times more efficient but, for many, the numbers don\u2019t stack up.",
